\begin_layout Title
On Sufficient Conditions for P-optimal Proof Systems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Nils Wisiol
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
This paper weakens the known sufficient conditions for the existence of
 p-optimal propositional proof systems.
 In 1997, Meßner and Torán proved that 
\begin_inset Formula $\EE=\NEE$
\end_inset

 is a sufficient condition for the existence of p-optimal proof systems.
 We are adopting their proof to show weaker conditions for the existence
 of p-optimal proof systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Introduction: Known Sufficient Conditions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\P=\NP$
\end_inset

 implies the existence of p-optimal proof systems trivially.
 The conditions was weakened in the eighties by Krajíček and Pudlák, which
 gave a proof that 
\begin_inset Formula $\E=\NE$
\end_inset

 is already sufficient.
 This result was improved further by Meßner and Torán, which showed that
 
\begin_inset Formula $\EE=\NEE$
\end_inset

 is sufficient.
 
\end_layout

